        "content": "<p>Here are two unicode symbols, and their use in mathlib</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Symbol</th>\n<th>Name</th>\n<th>vscode shortcuts</th>\n<th>uses in mathlib</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><code>⊥</code></td>\n<td>UP TACK</td>\n<td><code>\\bot</code>, <code>\\perp</code></td>\n<td><code>has_bot.bot</code>, mutually_singular (<a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/measure_theory.measure.mutually_singular\"><code>⊥ₘ</code></a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/measure_theory.vector_measure.mutually_singular\"><code>⟂ᵥ</code></a>)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code>⟂</code></td>\n<td>PERPENDICULAR</td>\n<td></td>\n<td>none</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>It would be nice to be able to use <code>⟂</code> (PERPENDICULAR) for geometry; but to do that, we'd also want <code>\\perp</code> to type it.</p>",
        "id": 327158463,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1676068305
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Does the following change look reasonable?</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Symbol</th>\n<th>Name</th>\n<th>vscode shortcuts</th>\n<th>uses in mathlib</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><code>⊥</code></td>\n<td>UP TACK</td>\n<td><code>\\bot</code></td>\n<td><code>has_bot.bot</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code>⟂</code></td>\n<td>PERPENDICULAR</td>\n<td><code>\\perp</code></td>\n<td>mutually_singular (<a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/measure_theory.measure.mutually_singular\"><code>⟂ₘ</code></a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/measure_theory.vector_measure.mutually_singular\"><code>⟂ᵥ</code></a>), possible geometry uses</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>",
